    <h1 id="Introduction">Using categories and tags</h1>

    <p>
      The Web Stories WordPress plugin provides two taxonomies for organizing your content in the WordPress admin: categories and tags.
      To add Categories and Tags to your stories, open the Web Stories editor and navigate to the Document tab, where you can find a dedicated Taxonomies panel.
    </p>

    <p class="img-wrap">
      <amp-img layout="intrinsic" width="316" height="625" src="./img/docs/how-to/taxonomies-panel.png" alt="A screenshot of the Web Stories Editor Document Panel highlighting the Taxonomies section with Categories and Tags options."></amp-img>
    </p>

    <p>
      You can also assign and view taxonomies at Stories > All Stories:
    </p>

    <p class="img-wrap">
    <amp-img layout="intrinsic" width="652" height="230" src="./img/docs/how-to/taxonomies-all-stories.png" alt="A screenshot of the All Stories screen with dedicated columns for categories and tags for listed stories."></amp-img>
    </p>

    <p>
      Note that adding a category or tag to a story does not change the story's URL unless you are using a custom configuration or another plugin that adds the taxonomy to the URL.
    </p>
